I would run one normal smoke test and one bad-template test before merging. Since 5C specifically changed template resolution/failure behavior, I would not skip the negative test.

1. Normal smoke test

Run this from the VM/host where pxe-content is running:

CID=pxe-content
rm -rf /tmp/pxe-phase5c
mkdir -p /tmp/pxe-phase5c
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/boot.ipxe \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase5c/boot.ipxe
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/generated/isos.txt \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase5c/isos.txt
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/generated/status.json \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase5c/status.json
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/index.html \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase5c/index.html
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/ks/rhel8-minimal.ks \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase5c/rhel8-minimal.ks
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/ui/background.png
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/rhel8/images/pxeboot/vmlinuz
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/rhel8/images/pxeboot/initrd.img
python3 -m json.tool /tmp/pxe-phase5c/status.json >/dev/null

Then check the new 5C fields:

grep -n '"generated_kickstarts"' /tmp/pxe-phase5c/status.json
grep -n '"template_source"' /tmp/pxe-phase5c/status.json
grep -n '"template_search_paths"' /tmp/pxe-phase5c/status.json
grep -n '"template_path"' /tmp/pxe-phase5c/status.json

Expected result: those fields show up in status.json.

Then make sure future placeholder profiles did not generate real boot targets:

if grep -En 'inst\.ks=.*(developer-workstation|security-baseline|security-luks|embedded-edge|small-disk)' /tmp/pxe-phase5c/boot.ipxe; then
  echo "ERROR: future profile generated a real boot target"
else
  echo "OK: future profiles do not generate real boot targets"
fi

Expected result:

OK: future profiles do not generate real boot targets

2. Bad-template test

This confirms 5C fails clearly when someone marks a non-minimal profile as implemented but the Kickstart template does not exist.

CID=pxe-content
podman exec -it "$CID" /bin/sh -lc '
rm -rf /tmp/pxe-bad-profiles /tmp/pxe-bad-output
mkdir -p /tmp/pxe-bad-profiles
cat > /tmp/pxe-bad-profiles/10-minimal.yml <<EOF
profile_id: minimal
title: Minimal Installs
install_label: Minimal
menu_target: minimal
implemented: true
show_in_main_menu: true
uefi: true
bios: true
supported_os:
  - rhel8
kickstart_template: "{{ os_id }}-minimal.ks.tmpl"
kernel_args:
  - inst.text
  - nomodeset
EOF
cat > /tmp/pxe-bad-profiles/20-developer-workstation.yml <<EOF
profile_id: developer_workstation
title: Developer Workstation Installs
install_label: Developer Workstation
menu_target: developer_workstation
implemented: true
show_in_main_menu: true
uefi: true
bios: true
supported_os:
  - rhel8
kickstart_template: missing-developer-template.ks.j2
kernel_args:
  - inst.text
  - nomodeset
EOF
set +e
PXE_SERVER=127.0.0.1 \
PXE_PROFILE_ROOT=/tmp/pxe-bad-profiles \
PXE_HTML_ROOT=/tmp/pxe-bad-output \
python3 /usr/local/bin/generate-pxe-content.py --once > /tmp/pxe-5c-bad.out 2>&1
rc=$?
set -e
cat /tmp/pxe-5c-bad.out
if [ "$rc" -eq 0 ]; then
  echo "ERROR: missing non-minimal template unexpectedly passed"
  exit 1
fi
if grep -Eq "developer_workstation|missing-developer-template|Searched|not found" /tmp/pxe-5c-bad.out; then
  echo "OK: missing non-minimal template failed clearly"
else
  echo "ERROR: failed, but not with the expected clear template message"
  exit 1
fi
'

Expected result:

OK: missing non-minimal template failed clearly

If both of those pass, I’d be comfortable merging 5C.